7356357100110482730.video_description: Replying to @Paxton Rigatoni Kitty  Ingredients  1/2 small sweet onion diced 3 tbs olive oil  3 cloves garlic minced  4 oz Italian sausage removed from the casing  1 tbs tomato paste  1 cup heavy cream  2 cups chicken/bone broth  1 cup dry rigatoni  1 dry basil 1 tbs Italian seasoning  1 cup frozen peas  1/4 cup grated parmesan  1. Add onion to a skillet with olive oil and sauté on medium for 3-4 minutes until onion is softened and translucent 2. Add 3 cloves garlic and Italian sausage. Sauté about 5 minutes or until your sausage is browned  3. Add in tomato paste,, chicken/bone broth, dry rigatoni, dry basil, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper to taste  4. Cover and heat over medium high heat until it starts to simmer.  5. Once simmering, remove the lid, add in frozen peas and heavy cream and allow to simmer for 10 minutes or until the rigatoni is al dente- stirring consistently so your pasta doesn’t stick  6. Stir in grated Parmesan and plate with red pepper flakes  #rigatonipasta #italianrecipes #pastarecipe
7356357100110482730.voice_to_text: This is one of my favorite pasta dishes in the entire world, the rigatoni piti from barpiti. But here's my one pop version so you can make it at home. I was seriously making this restaurant copycat so often that I renamed it the Rigatoni Kitty. You just saute your onions and sausage, and then your pasta cooks in the chicken broth. Add in your peas and heavy cream, a ton of parm, of course, and it comes out pretty close to the real thing, if I do say so myself. My favorite is when the peas get stuck inside the rigatone. Mmm.
